    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-09-16T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-09-16T13:00:00-05:00" n="697"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d697">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">823.01/23: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dearing</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-09-16T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 16, 1930—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>109. On Thursday, September 18, you will please inform the Foreign Minister that
                    you are instructed by the Government of the United States to enter into full
                    diplomatic relations with the new Peruvian Government, thus constituting
                    recognition thereof.</p>
                <p>An announcement of this will be made here late Wednesday afternoon.<note n="12"
                        xml:id="d697fn12">See press release issued by the Department of State on
                        September 17, 1930, <ref target="frus1930v01#pg_387">vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 387</ref>.</note> Until release here the
                    above should be treated as confidential. Similar action will be taken as to
                    Argentina and Bolivia.<note n="13" xml:id="d697fn13">See <ref
                            target="frus1930v01#pg_378">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, pp.
                            378</ref> ff. and <ref target="frus1930v01#pg_415">pp. 415</ref>
                        ff.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
